 Study end-point will be at 18 months after the continuous administration of nasal calcitonin or placebo and supplements as above.

 Bone mineral density will be measured by dual energy X-Ray absorptiometry (DXA) at the beginning of the study, and then at 9 and 18 months.

 The study subjects will be evaluated clinically and nutritionally at the beginning of the study, as well as every 3 months for the duration of the study.

 Laboratory values relevant to calcium homeostasis and bone turnover will be obtained every 3 months.

